70449", "createdAt": "2020-02-24T02:55:29Z", "author": {"login": "rolfyone"}, "path": "sync/src/test/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/sync/PeerSyncTest.java", "diffHunk": "@@ -375,6 +377,11 @@ void sync_handleEmptyResponse() {\n     // Check that the sync is done and the peer was not disconnected.\n     assertThat(syncFuture).isCompleted();\n     verify(peer, never()).sendGoodbye(any());\n+\n+    // check syncStatus\n+    UnsignedLong slot = peerSync.getSyncStatus().current_slot;\n+    assertThat(slot).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(peerSync.getSyncStatus().highest_slot);\n+    assertThat(peerSync.getSyncStatus().highest_slot).isGreaterThan(UnsignedLong.valueOf(0));", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "1f94f5b0bd3adafd36f119e6e01baf0d1c30be7e"}, "originalPosition": 17}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3MzYzMTY2MTUz", "url": "https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/1219#pullrequestreview-363166153", "createdAt": "2020-02-24T04:31:33Z", "commit": {"oid": "1f94f5b0bd3adafd36f119e6e01baf0d1c30be7e"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 3, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wMi0yNFQwNDozMTozM1rOFtVg2g==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wMi0yNFQwNDozOTo0NlrOFtVk-A==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM4MzA4MjcxNA==", "bodyText": "This needs to be in a synchronised block.  Both the read and write sides have to be synchronised for it to have any effect.", "url": "https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/1219#discussion_r383082714", "createdAt": "2020-02-24T04:31:33Z", "author": {"login": "ajsutton"}, "path": "sync/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/sync/PeerSync.java", "diffHunk": "@@ -63,6 +67,10 @@ public PeerSync(\n     final UnsignedLong latestFinalizedSlot = compute_start_slot_at_epoch(finalizedEpoch);\n     final UnsignedLong firstNonFinalSlot = latestFinalizedSlot.plus(UnsignedLong.ONE);\n \n+    this.startingSlot = firstNonFinalSlot;\n+    this.currentSlot = startingSlot;\n+    this.highestSlot = peer.getStatus().getHeadSlot();", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "1f94f5b0bd3adafd36f119e6e01baf0d1c30be7e"}, "originalPosition": 17}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM4MzA4MzQwMQ==", "bodyText": "The currentSlot is already available from ChainStorageClient.getBestSlot() and that will correctly show the last imported block, not just the last downloaded block.\nhighestSlot probably should be calculated from SyncManager as well since it's the highest slot of any peer, not just the slot of the peer we're syncing to at the moment.\nAnd then at that point you'd only have a single variable being updated here, so it could be volatile and remove all the synchronized.", "url": "https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/1219#discussion_r383083401", "createdAt": "2020-02-24T04:36:32Z", "author": {"login": "ajsutton"}, "path": "sync/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/sync/PeerSync.java", "diffHunk": "@@ -113,6 +121,7 @@ public void stop() {\n                   startSlot,\n                   peer.getId());\n               final UnsignedLong nextSlot = startSlot.plus(count);\n+              currentSlot = nextSlot; // might end up at highest + 1 but by then syncing is finished", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "1f94f5b0bd3adafd36f119e6e01baf0d1c30be7e"}, "originalPosition": 26}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM4MzA4Mzc2OA==", "bodyText": "We should be able to assert the exact highest slot as it should be the slot of the remote peer we set up.", "url": "https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/1219#discussion_r383083768", "createdAt": "2020-02-24T04:39:46Z", "author": {"login": "ajsutton"}, "path": "sync/src/test/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/sync/PeerSyncTest.java", "diffHunk": "@@ -161,6 +161,8 @@ void sync_stoppedBeforeBlockImport() {\n     when(peer.requestBlocksByRange(any(), any(), any(), any(), any())).thenReturn(requestFuture);\n \n     final SafeFuture<PeerSyncResult> syncFuture = peerSync.sync(peer);\n+    SyncStatus syncStatus = peerSync.getSyncStatus();\n+    assertThat(syncStatus.highest_slot).isGreaterThan(UnsignedLong.valueOf(0));", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "1f94f5b0bd3adafd36f119e6e01baf0d1c30be7e"}, "originalPosition": 5}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "2ec58079fd41e23410170a2832463234bc208a0e", "author": {"user": {"login": "macfarla", "name": "Sally MacFarlane"}}, "url": "https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/commit/2ec58079fd41e23410170a2832463234bc208a0e", "committedDate": "2020-02-24T23:54:35Z", "message": "Merge branch 'master' of github.com:PegaSysEng/artemis into 1180-syncing-slots"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "18e85e83beed17ce5af5e912c64bb2c946e34b60", "author": {"user": {"login": "macfarla", "name": "Sally MacFarlane"}}, "url": "https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/commit/18e85e83beed17ce5af5e912c64bb2c946e34b60", "committedDate": "2020-02-25T01:39:34Z", "message": "get current slot from storageClient and highest slot from SyncManager\n\nSigned-off-by: Sally MacFarlane <sally.macfarlane@consensys.net>"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3MzYzODMwMDYx", "url": "https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/1219#pullrequestreview-363830061", "createdAt": "2020-02-25T02:15:48Z", "commit": {"oid": "18e85e83beed17ce5af5e912c64bb2c946e34b60"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wMi0yNVQwMjoxNTo0OFrOFt2gKA==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wMi0yNVQwMjoxNTo0OFrOFt2gKA==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM4MzYyMzIwOA==", "bodyText": "nit: UnsignedLong.ZERO", "url": "https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/1219#discussion_r383623208", "createdAt": "2020-02-25T02:15:48Z", "author": {"login